programmes.show_description: How do they fashion cool clothing that can withstand the heat of a furnace, and how do they turn sea into land to create artificial islands? Plus, putting the fizz in champagne. S6, Ep14
How have they designed a car that can call the emergency services? How is metal turned into magnets? And how are the biggest ships propelled? S6, Ep15
Caterham 7. Mike surprises Elvis with a Caterham Seven, but the size of the restoration job is bigger than expected. Can they get it race-worthy in time? S18, Ep9
Peugeot 405. Mike has found a rare, 33-year-old Peugeot 405 while in Portugal. But finding parts isn't going to be easy. Can Mike and Elvis turn a profit? S18, Ep10
From Cornwall To Oxfordshire. Henry Cole and motorcycle guru Sam Lovegrove travel from Cornwall to Oxfordshire to rummage in some of Britain's most amazing sheds and make some cash. S1, Ep1
Buckinghamshire. Henry and Sam are in Buckinghamshire seeking hidden automotive gems to sell. They find stationary engines, traction engines and vintage petrol cans. S1, Ep2

Breakdowns And Complications. A failed plan sees the Gold Gypsies run out of time and options. Meanwhile, the Dirt Dogs uncover a huge find -but there's a catch. S1, Ep7
Risking Life And Limb. In the final week of the gold season, the Dirt Dogs gamble big to hit their tally. Kellie and Henri mount a last-chance hunt for big nuggets. S1, Ep8
The Bushmen dodge rockfalls in a potentially deadly new mine. The Fire Crew close in on a new deposit of black opal and the Boulder Boys struggle to drain their pit. S3, Ep7
The Bushmen are desperate for a breakthrough after a run of bad luck. And the Young Guns are under financial strain and fall out over their new mine. S3, Ep8

Cornwall. In Cornwall, Henry and Sam meet a collector whose cottage is full of memorabilia, penny farthings and lights of all description - watched over by Buster, the guard rabbit. S1, Ep4
Peter And Cat / RAF Truck. Henry and Fuzz view an exquisite collection of military and civilian vehicles in Guildford. What will they sell to the drummer from a British rock band? S5, Ep7
Vincent / Triumph 5TA. Henry and Fuzz sail over to the Isle of Wight. They meet Vince, a fanatical collector whose sheds are bursting with British and Japanese bikes. S5, Ep8
Lot of Bottle & Miner Bonanza. Angus sells a huge collection of unearthed Victorian bottles and vintage tins before finding a valuable haul of miners' strike memorabilia. S5, Ep7
What's Your Handle? Angus helps a daughter sell her late father's CB radios. And after losing their partners, he helps a new couple start their next chapter together. S5, Ep8
What's Occurring In Wales? On the second leg of Izzie Balmer and Mark Hill's first-ever road trip, they battle for bargain antiques in the towns and villages of Carmarthenshire. S27, Ep7
Treasures And Trinkets Abound. Doyenne of the jewellery world, Izzie Balmer and 20th century design whizz Mark Hill raid the antiques shops of Stroud, Cirencester and beyond. S27, Ep8
Mum Knows Best. Things appear to be on the up when they land a prestigious Morgan job, but a disastrous E-Type re-build prompts an emergency audit by Richard's mum. S5, Ep3
Slow Your Roll. The Opal Whisperers are on a mission to unearth something worthwhile from their newly excavated trench. Aging machinery slows The Bushmen down. S8, Ep16
Back To Burra. Bruce and John are back at Burra hunting the old mine pit and gaol. Meanwhile, Michael and Max are detecting Balmoral Baths in Sydney. S1, Ep8
How do they look after sharks at the world's biggest aquarium? How do they grow precious stones? And what does it take to build a luxury Bentley? S6, Ep16

Find out how they make military helicopters, how they design metro systems and how they engineer artificial reefs. S6, Ep20
Ferrari 348 - Italy. In northern Italy, Mike and Elvis tackle the last truly analogue Ferrari, the 348. And this one is in dire need of a cambelt change. S1, Ep1
Fiat 126 - Poland. In Poland, Mike and Elvis find a weathered Polski Fiat 126. After their restoration, they go on a snow-covered joyride alongside other loyal 126 fans. S1, Ep2

Five crews of gold hunters face all-new bonanzas, battles, heroism and heartbreak, as a new season dawns on the Western Australian Goldfields. S2, Ep1
As Gold Gypsies Chris and Greg Clark start their season with heartbreak, the Dirt Dogs hit a possible jackpot. And wild western team Ted and Lecky Mahoney hit the gold trail, hard. S2, Ep2
The Tunnel Rats are under extra pressure as rival miners close in on their claim. And, the Bushmen must brave an abandoned mine to remove a dead animal. S3, Ep9
The Bushmen confront a miner who has illegally dug their claim. The Young Guns must find a new source of opal when poisonous fumes force them to abandon their mine. S3, Ep10

West Country And Oxfordshire. Henry and mechanic Sam visit two amazing sets of sheds in the West Country and Oxfordshire, in search of a vintage treasure to buy, restore and sell. S1, Ep5
Cornish Surf. Henry and Sam scour a Cornish surf shack and find custom bikes, surf buggies and weird and wonderful objects of all kinds. Will they make some cash in Cornwall? S1, Ep6
Nick / Austin Champ. Henry and Fuzz are overwhelmed by Nick from Brackley's military collection. They leave with a vintage rarity, but will they find a buyer for something so unique? S5, Ep9
David / Ducati. Henry and Fuzz rummage through David's hoard of Italian bikes in Norfolk. They're smitten by his Ducatis and his rare Mot Guzzis, but just what will he sell? S5, Ep10
The Hunt for Lost Gold. A hunt for lost gold in a Glasgow flat proves a challenge for Angus. He also helps a widow with an emotional downsize. S5, Ep9
Eric Clapton & German Warship. Angus finds musical gems including Eric Clapton's old gear in an unusual home, and helps a grieving daughter sell her late mum's clockwork elephant. S5, Ep10
Wowed By Tribal Baby Hood. Izzie Balmer and Mark Hill motor through Oxfordshire and the Midlands searching for hidden treasures to take to auction. S27, Ep9
A Very Cuddly Grand Finale. Mark and Izzie's final outing, where they fall in love with cuddly toys, dumbwaiters, and early 20th century glass. Who will make the biggest profit? S27, Ep10
Super Models & Deco Delights. Angus unearths vintage toys and faces a downsizing dilemma. He auctions a collection of rare stamps, and some beloved Art Deco furniture. S6, Ep18
The team take on a unique bicycle sidecar designed for junior passengers. Plus, a Victorian sewing stand needs a lot of work, and a military drum gets a refresh. S5, Ep8
Metalworker Dominic is challenged to revive a rare and collectable 1930s seesaw. Meanwhile, embroidery expert Sara works on a hand-stitched bedspread. S5, Ep11
How do engineers build and control high-tech, unmanned aircraft? Plus, the process of removing caffeine from coffee is revealed. S8, Ep1
How do Japanese chefs prepare poisonous puffer fish and avoid killing their customers? How do Scots weave over 700 types of tartan for kilts? S8, Ep2
